            . I am the wife of Joseph Bolsover - he is a <rs id="t18270712-30-viclabel184" type="occupation">dealer in coals</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-30-victim254 t18270712-30-viclabel184"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18270712-30-crimeloc185">Moor-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270712-30-crimeloc185" type="placeName" value="Moor-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270712-30-crimeloc185" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-30-off182 t18270712-30-crimeloc185"></join>. This watch was silver, and worth 30s.; there was a key and ribbon to it - it hung in the parlour, behind the shop; I saw it safe about half a minute before it was stolen; the prisoner was in the parlour, alone - I had asked her to take a cup of tea with me; I had occasion to go into the yard, and on looking through the window I saw her take the watch down off the hook; she ran out as fast as she could with it - I ran in, and said to my man, "Run out, for that woman has taken my watch;" I have not found it. I did not see her again till last Wednesday; I did not know where she lived.</p>
               <p>
            
